Norway Banks May Need $9 Billion to Boost Capital, FSA Says

-- B y   J o n a s   B e r g m a n
-- 
2011-09-28T08:56:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/norway-banks-may-need-9-billion-to-boost-capital-fsa-says.html
Norway ’s largest lenders may need
30 billion kroner to 50 billion kroner ($9 billion) in external
funds to meet an “ambitious” strenghtening of core capital by
2 percentage points by 2013, Norway’s financial regulator said in 
a report today, citing its own calculations.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
